The paper deals with joint information embedding, lossless compression, and encryption, which are all related to information theory and multimedia. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the protection of the watermark against unauthorized parties, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper deals with the distortion between the composite signal and the covertext, which is related to image and video processing, and hence, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the equivocation of the watermark, which is related to privacy and anonymity, and hence, it could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
